          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">It=E2=80=99s been n=
early three years since the tragic shooting on the set of the Western film =
<i>Rust</i>, where a Colt .45 held by <b>Alec Baldwin</b> ended the life of=
 42-year-old cinematographer <b>Halyna Hutchins</b>. The ensuing criminal c=
ase has been rife with twists, starting with Baldwin=E2=80=99s perplexing i=
nterview with <b>George Stephanopolous</b> where he claimed to have not pul=
led the trigger. The charges of involuntary manslaughter were filed, then d=
ropped amid a report of a modified gun, only to be surprisingly <i>refiled<=
/i> earlier this year by an ambitious new prosecutor. With the trial finall=
y kicking off in Santa Fe this week, the question facing the jury is straig=
htforward: Did Baldwin fail to exercise due care by not checking the firear=
m for live rounds?<br/><br/>After the charges were renewed, SAG-AFTRA ralli=
ed to Baldwin=E2=80=99s defense,
emphasizing that =E2=80=9Can actor=E2=80=99s job is not to be a firearms or=
 weapons expert.=E2=80=9D Several witnesses echoed this defense during the =
April criminal trial of <i>Rust</i> armorer <b>Hannah Gutierrez</b>, who wa=
s convicted and sentenced to 18 months in prison. And yet, despite attempts=
 by Baldwin=E2=80=99s <b>Alex Spiro</b>-led A team at Quinn Emanuel to dism=
iss the charges, Judge <b>Mary Marlowe Sommer</b> found enough evidence of =
Baldwin=E2=80=99s potential negligence to proceed to trial. The focus of th=
e case has now coalesced around Baldwin=E2=80=99s mental state at the time =
of the incident.<br/><br/>The prosecution argues that Baldwin acted reckles=
sly, fully aware that he was handling a real weapon yet eschewing essential=
 safety protocols, including the risk of live and dummy rounds being mixed =
together. They=E2=80=99ve spotlighted his cavalier attitude during training=
 sessions with Gutierrez=E2=80=94he allegedly took selfies for his family=
=E2=80=99s entertainment=E2=80=94and say he violated decades-old movie set
safety protocols by pointing the gun at a person during rehearsals. In open=
ing statements later this week, prosecutors will lay out that case.<br/><br=
/>On the flip side, Baldwin=E2=80=99s defense frames the trial as an overze=
alous attempt to target a high-profile actor for headlines. They are contes=
ting the prosecution=E2=80=99s narrative, with attorney <b>Luke Nikas</b> s=
tating at a pretrial hearing yesterday, =E2=80=9CIn his mind, he didn=E2=80=
=99t think there was a live bullet in the gun,=E2=80=9D signaling a content=
ious battle ahead in Santa Fe over the next two weeks.<br/></td>
